{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Chilli oil","content":["Place all chilli oil ingredients into mixing bowl and heat <b>10 min\/70°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer into a jug and set aside to cool.","Once cooled, remove whole chillies from oil and set aside. Carefully pour oil through a funnel into a sealable jar or bottle. Add reserved chillies to the jar or bottle and seal.  Store chilli oil in a cool, dark place for up to 3 months."]},{"title":"Bean purée","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Wrap unpeeled garlic cloves in a piece of aluminium foil, place on a baking tray (20 x 30 cm) and roast for 20 minutes. Set garlic aside to cool for 10 minutes then remove outer skins.","Place all remaining bean purée ingredients, including peeled garlic cloves, into mixing bowl and blend <b>30 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and blend for a further <b>20 sec\/speed 7<b>."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["Spread bean purée over toasted baguette slices (crostini) and top with an anchovy fillet. Drizzle over a little of the reserved chilli oil and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Chilli oil","content":["200 g olive oil","1 tbsp dried chilli flakes","2 whole dried red chillies"]},{"title":"Bean purée","content":["3 garlic cloves, unpeeled","½ fresh red chilli, deseeded if preferred and cut it into halves (optional)","2 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","800 g canned cannellini beans, rinsed and drained (weight is pre-draining)","40 g olive oil","30 g lemon juice","½ tsp dried rosemary","½ tsp dried oregano","¼ tsp ground smoked paprika, to taste","¼ tsp sea salt, to taste","¼ tsp ground black pepper, to taste"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["40 - 50 g anchovy fillets, in oil, drained and separated","1 baguette loaf, thinly sliced and toasted"]}],"id":"r82196","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-P_vxA91nXTY\/XZMumD8UjWI\/AAAAAAAAaHQ\/yiAl_KM842ErMD4J1pothS36qcnCOJcVgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_MPUSxUEO76QhvijQ.png","title":"White bean purée and anchovy on crostini","publishedAt":"2015-05-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.5 g","fat":"8.5 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"8.5 g","calories":"535 kJ \/ 127 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sealable jar or bottle, funnel, baking tray (20 x 30 cm), aluminium foil, oven","hintsAndTricks":["The chilli flavour in the oil will intensify the longer it sits so if you want a real chilli kick we recommend making your oil in advance."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","45m","30 pieces"]}